==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''in [[promptu]]'' 'in readiness'. 

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/ɪmprɒmptju/

===Adjective===
'''impromptu'''
#[[Improvised]]; without prior [[preparation]]; [[extemporaneous]]; [[unplanned]].
#:''The party began with an impromptu rendition of 'Happy Birthday'.''


Impromptu is also a catergory in high school speech. The object is to make a humorous speech that is two to five minutes long
using a five minute time for composition. Participants draw subjects for their speech out of slips of paper. He/She can pick three 
but only use one topic.